  "prompt": "What are the end of service benefits of an ex-president of the USA? How much is the ex-president\u2019s pension? How much is he paid in allowances?",
  "response": "Here are the current benefits for U.S. ex-presidents:\n\nPension:\n- Annual pension of $221,400 (as of 2021)\n- Adjusted annually for cost of living increases\n\nAdditional Benefits:\n1. Office Space and Staff Allowance:\n- Up to $150,000 annually for office space and staff\n- Covers administrative and professional expenses\n\n2. Travel Expenses:\n- Lifetime Secret Service protection\n- Reimbursement for official travel related to presidential duties\n\n3. Medical Care:\n- Access to military medical facilities\n- Lifetime health insurance benefits\n\n4. Other Benefits:\n- Funeral expenses (up to $250,000)\n- Free mailing privileges\n- Transition expenses immediately after leaving office\n\nTotal Annual Cost:\n- Estimated between $400,000 to $500,000 per former president\n\nThese benefits are provided under the Former Presidents Act of 1958, which was designed to provide financial support and security to those who have served in the highest office of the United States.\n\nThe specific amounts are periodically adjusted by Congress and can change based on legislative updates.",
